



Dear Sir
Frederick Town [Md.]Sunday forenoon May 14th 1758



Yesterday afternoon the Post gave me your Letter of the 11th which I transmitted to Brigdr Forbes.1 I expect Govr Sharpe at this place every moment, and if I was at Winchester I coud do but little untill he & Mr Blair arrived.2 I shall be with you at furthest on tuesday morning which makes me not enter upon particulars as I am to see you so soon. I am with great Sincerity Dear Sir Your most obedient and most humble Servant

John St clair

